        <h2>What Are You Waiting For? Join Bonus+ </h2>
        <p align="justify">At DAN AP we are surprised that not all our Supporters are involved with our free promotional programs, like Bonus+. DAN Members are a highly targeted market so putting your business/product before this large group of divers seems like an obvious decision. It does not take much effort on your part to get involved. You simply provide our team with three images, your logo, a business description and an offer and we take care of the rest. So what are you waiting for?</p>
        <p><em>What is Bonus+?</em><br />
        A dedicated website that contains offers from Dive Businesses for DAN Members to redeem. </p>
        <p align="justify"><em>Benefit of Bonus+?</em><br />
        DAN Members are a highly targeted market. Many undertake numerous dive trips throughout the year and are often on the look out for a great deal. Being part of Bonus+ means your business will be seen by thousands of divers, and is likely to generate new business for you.</p>
        <p align="justify"><em>What is the cost?</em><br />
          Bonus+ offers a great NO COST advertising opportunity.<br />
          <br />
        All we ask is that you submit an offer of value. Please think beyond the standard &ldquo;10%&rdquo; off deal as savvy travellers seek more than this. </p>
        <p align="justify">          Try to create a bundle of offers, incorporating all aspects of your business, so that the diver will find the offer hard to resist. Keep in mind what will best appeal to a diver looking for their next dive adventure.</p>
        <p><em>What will my business receive?</em><br />
        A dedicated page on the Bonus+ website. All at no cost. The page includes:</p>
        <p>1. Your Corporate Logo<br />
          2. A Business Description<br />
          3. Three Photos of Your Choice (that best highlight your business/offer)<br />
          4. Full Business Contact Details, including Hotlink<br />
          5. Your &ldquo;Offer of Value&rdquo; for DAN Members.</p>
        <p align="justify"><em>How do I get involved?</em><br />
        All you need to do is <a href="mailto:marketing@danasiapacific.org">email</a> through the above elements and our team will create your dedicated webpage. It is that easy.</p>
        <p><a href="http://danasiapacific.org/bonusplus/">CLICK HERE</a> to visit the Bonus+ website.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;        </p>
        <h2 align="left">DAN AP Point-of-Sale Materials</h2>
		<p align="justify">Are you running low of DAN  promotional items? To re-stock your DAN point-of-sale materials all you need to  do is send an <a href="mailto:marketing@danasiapacific.org">email</a>. Follow the link below and  let us know which item/s you would like and in what quantity.</p>
        <p><a href="../sponsors/_pdf/DANAP_Promo_Materials.pdf">CLICK HERE</a> to view DAN AP's current promotional materials  range.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
        <h2>Are Your DAN Posters / Brochures Visible In-Store? </h2>
        <p align="justify">To highlight your status as a DAN Supporter and advocate of  dive safety it is vital that you position your DAN materials in a highly  visible location within your dive centre. It is also important to ensure the  DAN brochures/flyers are placed on your countertop in the DAN promotional stand  you have been provided.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
        <h2><strong>Which DAN Branch Do My Divers Join?</strong></h2>
        <p align="justify">          As you know, the Divers Alert Network has numerous branches,  with each looking after a dedicated region. The DAN branch that a diver joins  is generally dependent on where they reside. The below information should  assist you in directing your divers to the relevant DAN branch to apply for  coverage. </p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN Asia-Pacific</strong> <a href="http://www.danasiapacific.org">www.danasiapacific.org</a> <br />
        Residents of Australia, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, Fiji,  Indonesia, Malaysia, Vietnam, Singapore, Cambodia, Myanmar, Philippines,  Vanuatu, India, Solomon Islands, Brunei, Thailand, Hong Kong, Korea, China and  Taiwan.</p>
        <p><strong>DAN America:</strong> <a href="http://www.diversalertnetwork.org">www.diversalertnetwork.org</a><br />
        Residents of The United States and Canada</p>
        <p><strong>DAN Brazil:</strong><a href="http://www.danbrasil.org.br/"> www.danbrasil.org.br/</a><br />
        Residents of Brazil</p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN Europe:</strong> <a href="http://www.daneurope.org">www.daneurope.org</a><br />
        Residents of Geographical Europe, European Territories, and  Protectorates, with regional IDAN responsibility for the countries of the  Mediterranean Basin, the countries on the shores of the Red Sea, the Middle  East including the Persian Gulf, the countries on the shores of the Indian  Ocean north of the Equator, as well as the related overseas territories,  districts, and protectorates.</p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN Southern Africa:</strong> <a href="http://www.dansa.org">www.dansa.org</a><br />
        Residents of South Africa, Swaziland, Lesotho, Namibia,  Botswana, Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Angola, Zambia, Zaire, Malawi, Tanzania, Kenya,  Madagascar, Comoros, Seychelles, and Mauritius.</p>
        <p><strong>DAN Japan:</strong> <a href="http://www.danjapan.gr.jp">www.danjapan.gr.jp</a> <br />
        Residents of Japanese mainland and islands.</p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>DAN World: </strong><a href="http://www.diversalertnetwork.org/world/default.aspx">www.diversalertnetwork.org/world/default.aspx</a><br />
        Residents of the Caribbean, Polynesia, Micronesia and  Melanesia (except Fiji), Puerto Rico, Guam, Bahamas, British and US Virgin  Islands, Central and South America.</p>
        <p align="justify"><em>The branch of DAN a diver joins in dependent on the country  they reside. E.g. If your diver lives in Australia they need to apply for  coverage via DAN Asia-Pacific. </em></p>
        <p align="justify"><strong>IMPORTANT</strong><br />
        * It is vital to note that each DAN affiliate organisation  offers somewhat different coverage options. As such, applicants should be  encouraged to review the coverage options carefully on the above websites.</p>
        <p align="justify">* It is essential that divers understand what their DAN  coverage includes and also their policy restrictions. If a diver is unsure  please encourage them to contact the relevant DAN office.&nbsp; </p>
        <h2><strong>Until Next Time ....</strong></h2>
        <p align="justify">We will continue sharing with you important issues. We hope this information will further encourage you to prepare yourself, your team and your diving clients for a diving accident or illness. </p>
        <p align="justify">Being prepared takes several forms: having the skills to assist in a diving emergency, having a sufficient supply of oxygen on-hand to help the diver in trouble, and being a member of an organisation that is dedicated to helping divers in trouble and improving the safety of diving. </p>
        <p align="justify">If you have a question that you would like to be addressed we encourage you to send us an email. We are happy to assist you and your team as best we can. If you have any recommendations as how we can reach more divers in your area or how we can better work together, let us know.</p>
        <p>Let&rsquo;s work together to improve dive safety.</p>
        <p><em>Until next time safe diving,</em></p>
        <p>John Lippmann, Mel Cefai and the DAN Asia-Pacific Team</p>
